cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.RO, cs.LG

Reasoning: The paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with non-rigid structure from motion and sequential surface recovery. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of shape compression and heart reconstruction could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the detection of temporally disjoint rigidity, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves the use of prior shape knowledge, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics).
